      application/json" \ -h "x-api-key: your_api_key" \ ... ```  alternatively, you can use the username and [...]

    - post /listrecurringdetails
      get stored payment details

      ask issuer to notify the shopper

title: authentiq api
description: strong authentication, without the passwords.

endpoints:
  - delete /key
    revoke an authentiq id using email & phone. if called with `email` and `phone` only, a verification code will be sent by email. do a second call adding `code` to complete the revocation.
  - post /key
    register a new id `jwt(sub, devtoken)` or `jwt(sub, pk, devtoken, ...)` see: https://github.com/skion/authentiq/wiki/jwt-examples
  - delete /key/{pk}
    revoke an identity (key) with a revocation secret
  - get /key/{pk}
    get public details of an authentiq id.
  - head /key/{pk}
    head info on authentiq id
  - post /key/{pk}
    update properties of an authentiq id. (not operational in v4; use put for now) v5: post issuer-signed email & phone scopes in a self-signed jwt see: https://github.com/skion/authentiq/wiki/jwt-examples
  - put /key/{pk}
    update authentiq id by replacing the object. v4: `jwt(sub,email,phone)` to bind email/phone hash; v5: post issuer-signed email & phone scopes and put to update registration `jwt(sub, pk, devtoken, ...)` see: https://github.com/skion/authentiq/wiki/jwt-examples
  - post /login
    push sign-in request see: https://github.com/skion/authentiq/wiki/jwt-examples
  - post /scope
    scope verification request see: https://github.com/skion/authentiq/wiki/jwt-examples
  - delete /scope/{job}
    delete a verification job
  - get /scope/{job}
    get the status / current content of a verification job
  - head /scope/{job}
    head to get the status of a verification job

title: banking api

description:
this is a testing version of an api used for banking services.

endpoints:
1. post /customer/login: endpoint for user login. it receives a username and password in the request body to authenticate the user and issue a token for secure access.
2. post /customer/register: endpoint for user registration. it receives a username, password, and other personal information in the request body to create a new user account.
3. get /customer: endpoint for retrieving customer information. it requires a valid token to access and retrieves information about the authenticated user.
4. get /accounts: endpoint for retrieving a list of user accounts. it requires a valid token to access and returns a list of accounts associated with the authenticated user.
5. get /accounts/new: endpoint for creating a new account. it requires a valid token to access and receives account details in the request body to create a new account.
6. post /transfer/send: endpoint for initiating a funds transfer. it requires a valid token to access and receives transfer details in the request body to initiate the transfer between accounts.

title: branch locator api
description: the branch locator api provides information about bank branches, including their details, location, and contact information. the api is designed to comply with open banking standards and regulations.

endpoints:
- get /open-banking/v2.2/branches: returns branch details for all branches.
- get /x-open-banking/v2.2/branches/country/{country}: returns branch details for all branches in the specified country.
- get /x-open-banking/v2.2/branches/country/{country}/town/{town}: returns branch details for all branches in the specified town.
- get /x-open-banking/v2.2/branches/geo-location/lat/{latitude}/long/{longitude}: returns branch details for all branches within a specified radius of the specified latitude and longitude.
- get /x-open-banking/v2.2/branches/postcode/{postcode}: returns branch details for all branches within a 5 mile radius of the specified postcode.
- get /x-open-banking/v2.2/branches/sortcode/{sortcode}: returns branch details for a branch specified by its sort code.

category: banking
